correction.issue:
Parameter name inconsistency. EA wrote `-ProjectRoot` for PS1 parameters (matching v1 item 2.5). However, v2 update 2.4.v2 <signature_pattern_for_ps1> specifies `param([string]$BlarAIRoot = $(if ($env:BLARAI_ROOT) { $env:BLARAI_ROOT } else {       
  'C:\Users\mrbla\BlarAI' }), ...existing params...)`, and 2.5.v2 specifies wake_launcher gains `-BlarAIRoot`. The XML is internally inconsistent (v1 uses -ProjectRoot, v2 supersedes with -BlarAIRoot). For Stage 2 execution, the v2 canonical signature pattern is       
  authoritative — partly because the 4 G-1 PS1 scripts must rename their existing `$RepoRoot` to `$BlarAIRoot` (per 2.4.v2 per-tool descriptions), so consistency requires standardization.
